feat(dashboard): wire attachments UI — paperclip, paste, drag-drop

Backend support for attachments has been wired up for a while (turn POST
takes attachments[], the daemon now serves an upload route in the prior
commit). This connects the chat input to it.

Three add-paths, all funnel through the same upload routine:

- Paperclip button next to send/stop, opening a file picker with
  accept="image/*,application/pdf". Multiple selection allowed.
- Paste from clipboard: ClipboardEvent items with kind="file" are picked
  up and uploaded; native paste-as-text still works for non-file items.
- Drag-drop on the input wrap: dragenter/over/leave/drop handlers track
  a depth counter so nested children don't flicker the highlight, with
  a "Drop to attach" overlay during the drag.

Selected files render as removable chips above the textarea while
uploading; image chips show a 24px thumbnail of the local object URL.
On submit, ready (status="done") attachments go into the queued message
and the optimistic user bubble in the same shape the daemon expects:
sha256, filename, mime. Send is blocked while any chip is still
uploading so the message can never land without the file.

Object URLs created for image previews are revoked on chip remove and
on send to keep memory clean.
